>
	<p>
		MetaGPT is a revolutionary multi-agent framework that simulates a collaborative software development
		environment. By orchestrating multiple AI agents, each with specialized roles, MetaGPT transforms
		natural language requirements into production-ready applications.
	</p>

	<h2>Key Features</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Multi-Agent Collaboration: Simulates a complete software company workflow</li>
		<li>Role-Based Architecture: Each agent has specific responsibilities and expertise</li>
		<li>Structured Output: Generates comprehensive software artifacts including PRD, design, and code</li>
		<li>Extensible Framework: Easily customize and add new agent roles</li>
		<li>Quality Assurance: Built-in code review and testing processes</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>How It Works</h2>
	<p>
		When you provide a project requirement to MetaGPT, it triggers a cascade of collaborative actions:
	</p>
	<ol>
		<li>The Product Manager analyzes and clarifies the requirements</li>
		<li>The Architect designs the system structure and technical approach</li>
		<li>The Project Manager creates a detailed task breakdown</li>
		<li>Engineers implement the solution following best practices</li>
		<li>QA Engineers ensure code quality and functionality</li>
	</ol>

	<h2>Getting Started</h2>
	<p>
		To start using MetaGPT, you'll need Python 3.9+ and OpenAI API access. Installation is
		straightforward using pip:
	</p>
	<pre><code>pip install metagpt</code></pre>

	<h2>Community and Support</h2>
	<p>
		MetaGPT is an open-source project with a growing community. You can:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Contribute on <a href="https://github.com/geekan/MetaGPT">GitHub</a></li>
		<li>Join discussions in our community forums</li>
		<li>Follow our blog for latest updates and best practices</li>
		<li>Report issues and suggest improvements</li>
	</ul>
